Seize the chance to develop across 610 acres at Salcido Ranch, strategically located at the I-19 Exit 42 interstate exchange in the Tubac-Amado area. This property boasts 27 acres of land adjacent and visible from 1-19 with M-1 zoning, offering a wide range of possibilities, including industrial, commercial, agricultural, and residential development. With a dedicated highway exit making entry onto/from I-19 easy and the convenience of being just north of the Border Patrol Inspection station, travel is made hassle-free for those heading north. The M-1 zoning allows for light industrial uses as well as commercial ventures under B-1 and B-2 zoning. Additionally, there's potential for county-approved expansion of the M-1 zone. In addition to the 27 net usable acres, 583 additional acres are available for development, zoned G-R (General Rural), opening even more possibilities for residential, agricultural, and rural development. Water will not be an issue for development with 2 registered exempt commercial wells, 7 adjudicated domestic wells, and one stock pond. Located just 30 miles from Tucson and 30 miles north of the Nogales, AZ-Mexico border, Salcido Ranch is perfectly positioned for those looking to capitalize on cross-border commerce. It's also an ideal location for agricultural uses, including medical marijuana cultivation and dispensary operations.
